text:
This is actually a very sensitive topic as u can sense the tension midway and how many cuts there were in between. It may seem funny and entertaining to watch but this talk may have cause drifts/distance towards certain members...

Long Explanation: (don't read if ur close-minded)




























Ages is a very strict topic in Korea and when an older (by year, JW in this case) decides to be friends with a younger (MK), it shows the level of comfortability and closeness between the two because they are evidently willing to set aside their ages for friendship. Which is why a certain member seems sensitive about it. What I'm saying is Hyuck may feel threatened that Mark is now closer to someone else than him when for 8 years, he was his closest friend. But there's no one to blame here really, it just happens in friendships. Mark probably felt really sad for Jungwoo for being the only 98 liner and wanted to make him feel not alone but I guess Mark didn't think much of it at that time that it could have hurt Hyuckie. But I'm pretty sure they're all still chill and friends but yeah certain incidents like these happen in real life too. And I know I don't know them personally and I'm only an audience but it happens to anyone and from what I've observed here (scripted or not), it happened to them too.

text: i understand that korea has age ranks and stuff and i respect that and i understand that mark wants to keep the hyung and dongsaeng agenda with donghyuck but it makes me a little sad that for years hyuck has been trying to drop the formalities to be friends and has consistently been turned down, and seeing that its easy for mark to drop formalities with other members, i can see why hyuck would be desperate for any chance he gets to try to drop them too. maybe its just the cultural differences because where i grew up theres no age ranks or certain names to being friends with someone so its a bit of a hard thing to grasp but idk sometimes i just wish mark would let hyuck drop the formalities and carry on as friends without formalities . I do understand though that mark is fond of taking care of hyuck and thats wholesome on its own, and i know for a fact if mark dropped formalities with dream he would definitely get clowned 10x worse than he already does hehe, but its just a little sad for me to think about

text: In Korea, age is a very important part of a relationship.  Usually, people of the same age call each other as friends.  If even one year old is different, they have a different title to call each other and should use honorifics every time they talk. I think the reason it's like that is because Mark and Lucas are foreigners, so they really didn't think much about hierarchy, but if Lucas is Korean, he'll probably think about it a little bit more and find solution whether he decides to be friends with Jungwoo or called Mark 'hyung'. But when you looked at exo and nct relationship, it's getting confusing, because Taeil and Kai and Sehun are 94' liners, but Taeil only treated Sehun like same age friends but not to Kai (I think), but then Sehun and Johnny are 'friends' because I think Johnny called Sehun 'Sehunnie', without the 'hyung', and Johnny is a 95 liner, but then Johnny called Taeil a 'hyung' which is friend with Sehun. Okay, I'm just rambling. bye

text: For the people who cant really understand what they are joking about, in Korea you can only be 'friends' (chin-gu) and speak informally if you are born in the same year. However people born in the earlier months could still be considered as 'born in the same year' and can speak informally. As the age difference of jungwoo and mark is over one year but they still speak informally, haechan was asking them why they do that and should lucas also be able to speak to jungwoo informally and stuff about to whom should they speak informally and how they should count the age of others and stuff.
